.19–0.28 oz). Voice The song of Humblot's sunbird consists of a series of chipping notes, which are mixed up. Alarm and contact calls are a harsh scolding \"tssk, tssk\". Distribution and habitat Humblot's sunbird is endemic to Grand Comoro and Moheli in the Comoros. It is found in forest, gardens and scrub from sea level to 790 metres (2,590 ft) above sea level. Habits Humblot's sunbird feeds by gleaning and hover gleaning insects from the leaf tips of the fronds of the coconut palm. It is known to sip nectar from Cocos nucifera, Cussonia spp, Eucalyptus and Impatiens spp. The nest is made of fine grass, covered with moss and lined with milkweed strands and attached to with moss to a branch. Laying is in August and September. Subspecies There are two subspecies: Cinnyris humbloti humbloti A. Milne-Edwards & Oustalet, 1885: Grand Comoro, in Comoro Is. Cinnyris humbloti mohelicus Stresemann & Grote, 1926: Mohéli Etymology The scientific name commemorates the French naturalist Léon Humblot. References", "shortSummary": "Humblot's sunbird (Cinnyris humbloti) is a species of bird in the family Nectariniidae. It is endemic to the islands of Grand Comoro and Mo…", "imageUrl": "https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/8/85/Humblot%E2%80%99s_sunbird.jpg", "kingdomId": "taxonomy-kingdom-animalia", "phylumId": "taxonomy-phylum-chordata", "classId": "taxonomy-class-aves", "genusId": "taxonomy-genus-cinnyris", "speciesId": "taxonomy-species-cinnyris-humbloti", "taxonomyIds": {"kingdom": "taxonomy-kingdom-animalia", "phylum": "taxonomy-phylum-chordata", "class": "taxonomy-class-aves", "genus": "taxonomy-genus-cinnyris", "species": "taxonomy-species-cinnyris-humbloti"}, "expandable": true, "x": -16.31, "y": 0.69, "z": -410.05}], "links": [{"key": "bird-humblot-s-sunbird-b064415c__belongs_to_species__taxonomy-species-cinnyris-humbloti", "source": "bird-humblot-s-sunbird-b064415c", "target": "taxonomy-species-cinnyris-humbloti", "relation": "belongs_to_species", "label": "属于种